  "text": "Semantic congruence can play a role in the integration of auditory and visual information (review in [CITATION_1] ). A recent study investigated the effect of object categories in auditory-visual integration [CITATION_2] . Using fMRI and identification rates, they showed specific multisensory associations for biologically relevant stimuli (human voice and faces), compared to non-biologically relevant stimuli (cell phones). A first question addressed in the present study is to measure the processing time for identification of a biologically relevant category compared with to a non-biologically relevant one, when object information is presented in several sensory modalities (auditory and visual).",
